			    STPJS 308</div>
  <p class="cont">God in any age of the world? I can never find much to say in expounding a text. A man never has
  half so much fuss to unlock a door, if he has a key, as though he had not, and had to cut it open with
  his jack-knife.</p>
  <p class="std">The main object was to build unto the Lord a house<span class="footRef">1</span> whereby He could reveal unto His people
  the ordinances of His house<span class="footRef">2</span> and the glories of His kingdom,<span class="footRef">3</span> and teach the people the way of
  salvation;<span class="footRef">4</span> for there are certain ordinances and principles that, when they are taught and practiced,
  must be done in a place or house built for that purpose.<span class="footRef">5</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Principles of the Gospel Never Change</div>
  <p class="std">It was the design of the councils of heaven before the world was,<span class="footRef">6</span> that the principles and laws
  of the priesthood<span class="footRef">7</span> should be predicated upon the gathering of the people in every age of the world.
  Jesus did everything to gather the people, and they would not be gathered, and He therefore poured
  out curses upon them.<span class="footRef">8</span> Ordinances instituted in the heavens before the foundation of the world,<span class="footRef">9</span> in
  the priesthood, for the salvation of men, are not to be altered or changed.<span class="footRef">10</span> All must be saved on the
  same principles.<span class="footRef">11</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Salvation for the Dead</div>
  <p class="std">It is for the same purpose that God gathers together His people in the last days,<span class="footRef">12</span> to build unto
  the Lord a house<span class="footRef">13</span> to prepare them for the ordinances and endowments, washings and anointings,<span class="footRef">14</span>
  etc. One of the ordinances of the house of the Lord is baptism for the dead.<span class="footRef">15</span> God decreed before the
  foundation of the world that that ordinance should be administered in a font prepared for that
  purpose in the house of the Lord.<span class="footRef">16</span> &ldquo;This is only your opinion, sir,&rdquo; says the sectarian. * * *</p>
  <p class="std">If a man gets a fullness of the priesthood of God<span class="footRef">17</span> he has to get it in the same way<span class="footRef">18</span> that Jesus
  Christ obtained it, and that was by keeping all the commandments<span class="footRef">19</span> and obeying all the ordinances
  of the house of the Lord.<span class="footRef">20</span></p>
  <p class="std">Where there is no change of priesthood, there is no change of ordinances, says Paul.<span class="footRef">21</span> If God
  has not changed the ordinances and the priesthood, howl, ye sectarians!  If he has, when and where
  has He revealed it? Have ye turned revelators? Then why deny revelation?<span class="footRef">22</span></p>
